  "verdict": "POSITIVE PARTIAL \u2014 strong",
  "verdict_text": "Multiple structural findings, but no single closed-form C = HK \u00d7 Vol \u00d7 n^p fits the family universally. Best reading: C is a QUOTIENT of two power laws with separately-converging Weyl/heat-kernel scaling, and each diagram topology has its own quotient. The dictionary is below.\n\nKey structural findings:\n  \u2605 graph_VP_trace ~ \u221a\u03c0 * n_max asymptotically (ratio \u2192 1.00 at n=3,4,5)\n  \u2605 \u03b2(C_VP) = \u03b2(continuum_VP) \u2212 \u03b2(graph_VP) verified to machine precision\n  \u2605 C_VP/C_SE \u2248 3/29 stable to CV 0.83%\n  \u2605 F2_graph_scalar(n) ~ 3.4950 * n^(-0.5693), CV 0.143% (extremely tight power law)\n\nNumerical summary:\n  - \u03b2_VP = +1.4789, \u03b2_SE = +1.4773, \u03b2_F2_asymp = +0.5693\n  - C_VP/C_SE mean = 0.10354 \u2248 3/29 (CV 0.83%)\n"
}